'''Sohail Ahmed''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|سہیل احمد}}}}), best known as '''Azizi''' ({{lang-ur|{{Nastaliq|عزیزی}}}}), is a [[Pakistani]] [[comedian]] and [[Stage (theatre)|stage]] and [[TV]] [[actor]]. He is notable for comedy stage and TV dramas based in [[Lahore]].<ref name=tv.com>[http://www.tv.com.pk/celebrity/Sohail-Ahmed/306/biography, Profile of TV comedian Sohail Ahmed on tv.com.pk website], Retrieved 26 September 2017</ref>
== Career == He improvises dialogue during stage plays. In January 2009, Sohail plays the character ''Azizi'' in the show [[Hasb-e-Haal]] on [[Dunya News]], where he does humorous commentary on current affairs and other topics.<ref>{{Cite report |author=Anne Geniets|date=February 2011|title=Trust in international news media in partially free media environments|url=https://reutersinstitute.politics.ox.ac.uk/fileadmin/documents/Publications/Working_Papers/Trust_in_International_News_Media.pdf|publisher=Reuters Institute for the Study of Journalism|page=67|accessdate=22 February 2014}}</ref> Most of the TV shows that he has acted in have been on [[Pakistan Television Corporation]].<ref name=tv.com /> Sohail Ahmed prefers to use unplanned dialogue during comedy shows.<ref>[http://urduwire.com/people/Sohail-Ahmed-Azizi_315.aspx, Profile of Sohail Ahmed on urduwire.com website], Retrieved 26 September 2017</ref>
=== Stage dramas === * ''[[Shartiya Mithay]]''<ref name=pak101>[http://www.pak101.com/c/celebrities/bio/318/Comedians/Sohail_Ahmed, Profile of TV Comedian Sohail Ahmed on pak101.com website], Retrieved 26 September 2017</ref> * ''Kaali Chaadar'' * ''Feeqa In America''
=== List of television shows === * ''[[Hasb-e-Haal]]'' comedy show on [[Dunya News]] in 2016<ref name=tv.com /> * ''[[Ullu Baraye Farokht Nahi]]'' drama on [[Hum TV]] in 2013
=== Films === * ''[[Punjab Nahi Jaungi]]'' * ''[[Jawani Phir Nahi Ani 2]] ''
==Awards and honors== * [[Pride of Performance]] Award by the [[President of Pakistan]] in 2011<ref name=Tribune/> * [[Sitara-i-Imtiaz]] (Star of Excellence) Award by the [[President of Pakistan]] in 2013<ref>[https://tribune.com.pk/story/421848/recognising-excellence-manto-among-192-recipients-of-top-civil-awards/ Sohail Ahmed's Sitara-i-Imtiaz Award listed on The Express Tribune (newspaper)], Published 14 August 2012, Retrieved 26 September 2017</ref>
